comment:
Listen, I also hate AH with a passion for this whole bullshit. But I'm not gonna give my hopes up for this new report mainly cause pretty much the exact same rumor came out months ago. So honestly, if this ends up false, I wouldn't be very disappointed. 
However, if this does end up true, I wouldn't be very shocked either. It seems that one of the narratives that the media wants to push is that JD and AH were both equally abusive to each other (which we know isn't the case). To me, it seems like because of all the bad PR Warner Bros received from firing JD, Warner Bros wants to go from the narrative that JD is the sole abuser to that both were equally abusive. So if this report is true, and Emilia Clarke does replace AH, then WB will see it as an accomplishment, as they'll see it as the controversy not being their problem anymore. Only problem for them with this plan, is that the public knows the truth. JD may have been on a lot of drugs, but he never actually absued AH. She actually abused him, verbally,physically, and mentally. So this "equally abusive" narrative isn't gonna work with us. So the general public is still gonna be happy that AH is gone, but also still gonna be pissed that JD is still gone aswell. So the Bad PR is still kinda there (if this report is true, that is).
